jdbcDriverInfo.driverName: jTDS Type 4 JDBC Driver for MS SQL Server and Sybase

jdbcDriverProperty.name: APPNAME
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The application name advertised by the driver.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: AUTOCOMMIT
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set the autocommit mode of newly created connections.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: BATCHSIZE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The number of statements to submit at once. Batches are broken up in pieces this large.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: BINDADDRESS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The IP address of the local interface that jTDS should bind to when connecting to a database via TCP/IP.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: BUFFERDIR
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The directory to buffer data to.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: BUFFERMAXMEMORY
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The global buffer memory limit for all connections (in kilobytes).

jdbcDriverProperty.name: BUFFERMINPACKETS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The minimum number of packets per statement to buffer to memory.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: CACHEMETADATA
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set to true to enable the caching of column meta data for prepared statements.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: CHARSET
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Server character set for non-Unicode character values.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: DATABASENAME
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database name.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: DOMAIN
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The domain used for authentication.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: INSTANCE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database server instance.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: LANGUAGE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The language for server messages.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: LASTUPDATECOUNT
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Return only the last update count on executeUpdate.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: LOBBUFFER
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The amount of LOB data to buffer in memory before caching to disk.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: LOGFILE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set the name of a file for the capture of logging information.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: LOGINTIMEOUT
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The time to wait for a successful login before timing out.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: MACADDRESS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Hex-encoded client MAC address.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: MAXSTATEMENTS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The maximum number of statements to keep open. This is only a target for the cache.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: NAMEDPIPE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Use named pipes to connect instead of TCP/IP sockets.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PACKETSIZE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The network packet size (a multiple of 512).

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PASSWORD
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database password.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PORTNUMBER
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database server port number.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PREPARESQL
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Use stored procedures for prepared statements.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PROCESSID
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The process ID reported by the driver.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: PROGNAME
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The program name advertised by the driver.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SENDSTRINGPARAMETERSASUNICODE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: If strings should be sent as unicode values.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SERVERNAME
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database server hostname.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SERVERTYPE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The type of database (1 is SQL Server, 2 is Sybase).

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SOCKETKEEPALIVE
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Use TCP/IP socket keep alive feature.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SOCKETTIMEOUT
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The TCP/IP socket timeout value in seconds or 0 for no timeout.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: SSL
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set the SSL level.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: TCPNODELAY
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Enable/disable TCP_NODELAY

jdbcDriverProperty.name: TDS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database server protocol.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USECURSORS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Use SQL Server fast forward only result sets for forward only result sets.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USEJCIFS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Force use of jCIFS library on Windows for connecting via named pipes.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USEKERBEROS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set to true to use Kerberos as the authentication mechanism.|N|true,false

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USELOBS
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Map large types (IMAGE and TEXT/NTEXT) to LOBs vs. String/byte[].

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USENTLMV2
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set to true to send LMv2/NTLMv2 responses when using Windows authentication

jdbcDriverProperty.name: USER
jdbcDriverProperty.description: The database user.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: WSID
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Workstation ID or client host name override. Will be stored in master.dbo.sysprocesses, column hostname.

jdbcDriverProperty.name: XAEMULATION
jdbcDriverProperty.description: Set to false to use the Microsoft Distributed Transaction Coordinator.

schemaCrawlerInfo.schemaCrawlerAbout:
SchemaCrawler 14.05.04 Copyright (c) 2000-2016, Sualeh Fatehi.
SchemaCrawler is a database schema discovery and comprehension tool. You can search for database schema objects using regular expressions, and output the schema and data in a readable text format. You can find potential schema design issues with lint. The output serves for database documentation is designed to be diff-ed against other database schemas. SchemaCrawler also generates schema diagrams.
